Connect with : 
	$ git config --global user.email "Your@email.com"
	$ git config --global user.name "Your name"

First, initialise the repository with :

	$ git init

Placed into the folder :

	$ git add yourFile.extension
	$ git commit -m "What you've done now"

If the file had already been added :

	$ git commit -a -m "What you've done now"

If you want to read all the commit made :

	$ git log

If you want to chech an old commit :

	$ git checkout SHAcommit 

	SHA = commit's id

	and then :
	
	$ git checkout master

	to come back

If you want to edit you last commit :

	$ git commit --amend -m "You're message"

If you want to erase all the change you've done that you didn't commit already :

	$ git reset --hard
